codex
I have the fix direction. The failing assumption is `warmupPeriod > 0`; on this fork it is `0`, but `stake(..., claimNow=false)` still creates a warmup liability that remains excluded from `circulatingSupply()` until claimed, so the same insolvency root cause is still reachable if at least two epochs are immediately overdue. I’m rewriting the verifier around that path and switching funding preference to alternate public direct-FLOOR liquidity routes first, with V2 flash-swap kept as fallback.
